## Appendix: Quick Reference

### Most Important Queries

```sql
-- Count total projects
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM projects;

-- Search by keyword
SELECT * FROM projects p
JOIN project_keywords pk ON p.project_id = pk.project_id
JOIN keywords k ON pk.keyword_id = k.keyword_id
WHERE k.keyword_text LIKE '%marine%';

-- Projects by cluster
SELECT p.*, tc.cluster_name
FROM projects p
JOIN project_clusters pc ON p.project_id = pc.project_id
JOIN thematic_clusters tc ON pc.cluster_id = tc.cluster_id
WHERE tc.cluster_name = 'Pollution Prevention & Reduction';

-- Document a synergy
INSERT INTO synergies (synergy_title, synergy_type, description, identified_date)
VALUES ('New Synergy', 'Knowledge Exchange', 'Description here', CURDATE());
```

### Key Table Relationships

```
projects (main table)
    ├── project_organizations → organizations
    ├── project_regions → regions
    ├── project_clusters → thematic_clusters
    ├── project_keywords → keywords
    └── synergy_projects → synergies
```

### KPI Tracking at a Glance

```sql
-- All KPIs in one query
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM projects) as total_projects,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM thematic_clusters WHERE is_active = TRUE) as active_clusters,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM synergies WHERE synergy_status IN ('Confirmed','Active')) as active_synergies,
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT session_id) FROM search_logs WHERE search_timestamp >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY)) as weekly_users;
```

